I"q<h4 id="skills">skills</h4>
<ul>
  <li>slow down your speaking speed
    <ul>
      <li>select your words carefully</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>give yourself time to think
    <ul>
      <li>relax</li>
      <li>“that’s a good question. Let me think for a moment”</li>
      <li>“I haven’t thought about it beofre … “</li>
      <li>“Well … I suppose … “</li>
      <li>“well, during the day …”</li>
      <li>“In the meantime why don’t we …”</li>
      <li>“It’s been a long time since … “</li>
      <li>“Sorry to trouble you … but … “</li>
      <li>“would you mind if …”</li>
      <li>“oh! come on” …</li>
      <li>“I’m just kidding … “</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>learn complete sentences</li>
  <li>learn to listen
    <ul>
      <li>listen what others are saying</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>practice asking questions</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>“what are your views on that?”</li>
      <li>“How about you, what do you think?”</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>produce english by writing</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="polite">polite</h4>
<p>request - can, could, man, might 
“Can I have .., please?”</p>

<p>decline - “That is a good idea. I would like to join in but I have another appointment today.”</p>

<p>sorry - “I want to apologise.”  “I owe you an apology”  “my mistake”  “I want to apologise for my behavior / to someone”  “I sincerely apologise” .. “I take full responsibly …”</p>

